
4 Tbsp butter
1/2 cup Thick cut bacon, diced
1/2 cup diced onion
2 cups chicken broth
1/2 cup red wine
1 large apple, peeled and sliced
2 Tbsp apple cider vinegar
2 tsp white sugar
4 whole cloves
3 bay leaves
1/4 tsp ground nutmeg
1 pinch ground cinnamon
salt and pepper to taste
2 1/4 lbs shredded red cabbage

1. Melt butter in stockpot (medium high heat)
2. stir in bacon and cook until just beginning to crisp
3. Add onions, stir until lightly browned (6 to 8 minutes)
4. Stir in chicken broth, red wine, apple slices, vinegar
5. Bring to boil
6. Stir in sugar, cloves, bay leaves, nutmeg, cinnamon, salt, pepper
7. Stir in red cabbage.
8. Cover.  Reduce heat to low, simmer 30 to 45 minutes

